# Regulatory Disclosures Insurance Discontinued Member Refund Indicator

## identifier
de8997

## type
boolean

## definition
Indicate if the member discontinues cover mid term and contributions (after allowing for administration charges) are refunded to the member for the unexpired period of cover.

## guidance
A choice of TRUE/FALSE values
TRUE = in the event of the member wanting to discontinue cover mid-term, the member receives a pro-rata refund of contribution paid
FALSE = in the event of the member wanting to discontinue cover mid-term, the member does not receive a pro-rata refund of contribution paid

## syntax
### xbrl
- name=RegulatoryDisclosures.InsuranceDiscontinuedMemberRefund.Indicator
- classification=baf/bafot/bafot.02.07
- period=duration
